Comment:
I remember when this song came out,, I lost my job, had no money, my girlfriend back then dumped me and eventually I lost my house. I listened to this song like a thousand times, it really helped me through that horrible time and I could really relate to it. Seen Passenger a few times live and every time his concerts were so comforting and peacefully. Now here we are almost 8 years later after this song came out, a solid job, a loving girl and we bought a house a few months back.

Life is a rollercoaster and it will always have it's ups and downs. No matter how bad and lonely you feel at some point, things will always get better in the end.

Thank you Mike for your amazing music!

Comment: I watched her leave for her flight on a cool day in mid August. Her dad got a new job offer and she had to go away. We always had this thing where we asked each other questions like if I hurt you would you still love me? And the answer would be "Always". I hit a few rough bumps in the road in the months that past. A year after she left I received a letter from her that had a picture of her and I at the fair. I flipped it over and written in black sharpie was "Always". I teared up and called her and we had a long conversation about our lives. She started college at a university for psychology. I talked to her about us and if we could still make it work but it seemed uncertain. 3 years later at our wedding I was in the bathroom and I took my ring off to wash my hands and as I was Putting it back on I saw the words "Always" engraved on the inside. I immediately remembered all the good times we had and it touched my heart like I've never felt so emotional in my entire life until that moment. There is no one in this world I would want to be with.

Comment:
Not so long ago my girlfriend and I were listening to this song. We both loved it and then one day she collapsed when we were out. I came to find out she had Stage 4 Pancreatic Cancer and was months away from dying. On her last day of life she asked me to put this song on. We listened to this song, on repeat for 6 hours, 22 minutes, and 33 seconds until she passed..... That was 2 years ago. Today I got an email from her parents with this song attached and a letter that she had written. 
It said: ‚ÄúI was wrong not to tell you sooner about my condition. I thought if I did you would of left me. But you stayed by my side the entire time. For that I love you. Will see you in another life‚Äù.
Can‚Äôt listen to this song ever again without having that go through my head....
My advice for anyone is hold who you love close by and tell them you care for them, because you never know when something bad will happen.

so, we met in 2nd grade when she moved to my school (in Kentucky) from Hawaii. at the time i had a different friend, let's call her "C". so, me and C had been friends since kindergarten. i knew that C was going to go into homeschooling at the end of the year, so i was feeling really sad and tried to make some new friends. at first i hated H because i thought she was trying to steal C from me. but after a while me, C, and H became a group. as it neared the end of the year, i met this random boy, we will call him "B". so, when i met B i didn't know what to think because i had only had female friends before this. i started to develop feelings for B. B didn't like my other friends, so i wasn't sure how to feel or what to do since i had to choose between B (who i fell really hard for), or C and H. it was the end of second grade, and me and H said our last goodbyes to C. we never saw C again. in 3rd grade, ms and H were in different classes. me and B were in the same class again. me and B had other friends (which aren't important enough to name.) and at this point i had H, and me and B's friend group. B hated H. i ended up telling H about my feelings for B. then i told a few other people. as expected, B found out. B started to drift away from me, and those other friends followed. i tried to talk to B but he didn't want anything to do with me. by the end of the year, all i had was H. then the year ended. when 4th grade started, i was still heartbroken over B. B thought i was weird and hated me at this point. H told me she had something to tell me. H told me that she was moving schools and probably wouldn't be seeing me in 5th grade. i was heartbroken. H was all i had, and we still talked about C sometimes, and finding C. it was the end of the fourth grade year. me and H said our final goodbyes, and i was on my own. when 5th grade started, i found out that B was going to the same middle school as me. to be honest, at this point i was pretty much a stalker. i could understand why he would hate me now, because i started to be obsessive, but, you know, first loves, amirite? but seriously, i was so excited. over the years everyone at my elementary had found out about my crush, and since middle school was starting, it would be a secret again, right. yep. too much of a secret. i did my whole sixth grade year virtual and thought of it as the perfect opportunity to escape my feelings for B. nope. actually, more of a chance to embrace them. i know this sounds dumb, but i would just stare at his black zoom box with his name. goofy smile on my face,  just remembering. over the years i had faked so many crushes to try and get away from this one, and i was just thinking how bad of a stalker i was to B. he was introvert, and i am (and have always been) extrovert. to try and distract myself from this crush, i emailed my old friend, H. I didn't know if that email even worked anymore, but surprise. i got an email back. she told me her discord, and i told her mine. we stayed in contact ever since. now, i had another problem. i had an online friend, E, who introduced me to her online friend, R. me and E didn't really contact anymore, and me and R became closer. eventually, i caught feelings for R so i confessed to her. she said she liked me, too, and i thought i escaped. i introduced H to R and R hated H. R brainwashed me into thinking H didn't care about me. it was just me and R now. but at the end of my 6th grade year i found out i needed to go to summer school. i got my phone taken until i finished it. (mind you, me and R had made plans to literally live together and get married in the future btw. by this time i had forgotten about B. i was in summer school, doing my work, yk, as it goes. when i finished, though, everything changed. i went to text R and tell her i was done, but what i opened her contact to was crushing. "i got a girlfriend 2 weeks ago and i was scared to tell you so i dont have a crush on you anymore." that's it. we got into a massive argument, i ended up cutting off all contact with her. i was alone again. everything had gotten so bad. i started thinking about B again. how had an innocent little childhood crush turned into this? i was so mad at myself for letting it get this out of control. i didn't like his as much, but memories, you know?  by the start of 7th grade, i had stopped thinking about him. my friendship with H had been revived, but H wasn't the same, sweet, loving soul. H is now just kinda depressed, i'm sure. H went to visit her grandma in SC right as covid started and is now stuck with her, so now lives there. i'm not the same either, though, so i can't complain. i have new friendships now, and my life is starting to look up. i'm homeschooled, but in the time that i was going to  in-person, i made a decent best friend (lets call them "G") me and G are always talking and laughing, and it's the healthiest friendship i've had in my whole life. i know that i've escaped my crush on B, and i know this sounds stupid, but it kinda saved me. because obsessing over someone who you haven't spoken to in 4 years isn't healthy. anyways, 7th grade ends in May 2022, and i'm the happiest i've been in a long time. 







TL:DR 

my crush that i chased around my whole life and the story of all my greatest (and worst) friendships. my story.

Comment: This song bring backs old memories of old feelings. It feels so nostalgic. The first time I heard this song wayback years ago I was deeply hurt and heartbroken. The Lyrics spoke so much to me: it embodied how far I can sacrifice if I love someone. The year this song was released was also the year I chose to let go of someone I love. It would have been nice to tell you guys that we ended up together but sadly, we didn't. However, something good came out from letting him go. I learned to love myself and God gave me someone who loves and cherishes me more. I don't feel like i'm not enough  or a burden, no insecurities or whatsoever about my relationship. Now I'm getting married to the man whom I met when I chose to let go. Now, this song reminds of how far I've came after I moved on from that pain. May the one who read this find their joy and healing as well. üòäüòä

Comment:
To all of you listening to this song during the quarantine, who may be feeling lonely or distant:
It's not the end of the road. If you truly believe that you're at rock bottom, then remember from that point, there's only one way left to go, and that's up.
This won't last forever. One day, most likely within a few months, we'll be resuming life as normal, and you'll be able to see all of the people you missed during the quarantine.
And this applies to relationships too - there's someone out there for you. Keep your chin up and don't give up. But most importantly, be yourself. When people notice you being true to yourself, it's a feeling like no other. And you can be happy to have somebody else.

I'm 18 and I haven't had a real relationship yet. To all of those in my boat, or those of you who are listening to this song and reading the comments amidst a breakup or loneliness, know that just a few months ago, I was doing the exact same thing. It's not the end, and plenty of us are with you. Keep your chin up, be yourself, and be great. Don't give up. You matter, and people *will* notice that you matter. :)

Comment:
It's weird how true this song is lol 

Me and my ex girlfriend broke up a 6 years relationship around 4/5 months ago, but it was a healthy end where she said she didn't want it anymore, and I totally respected that, even though I still wanted her.... I was always a very caring and passionate boyfriend, and she was a bit colder and less intense with things, but now that I'm outside of that relationship I noticed how little value she gave me before. Not only naturally due to her personality, but with other things too, things I accepted as "normal" but it was the minimum. It's funny because a few weeks ago she started messaging me wanting to go back and try it again, saying she missed me and that I was the love of her life...  She let me go, now she knows she loved me... But after these 4 months away, I noticed how other people can make me feel so much better about my self, in ways she just didn't care to.

So if you're reading this and you've recently broken up. Give your heart time, I felt like I really wanted to go back with her the same week we ended, but months after, I feel totally different. Give yourself time, and think with care and without the influence of missing what you had, then you can make your decisions with a clearer mind.

Also let me know if you need any help at all or just want to chat, these moments are hard! @allan_urique

Comment:
So I owe so much to this song Mr Rosenberg, and I thank you so very, very much for writing this amazing track which has become a bit of a repetitive theme in my adult life.
Long ago when I saw moonbeams come out of piles of shit, an example of this being my ex husband, I married somebody who I thought had the potential to grow into a decent human being, but sadly, did not, and after many many years of suffering and disrespect, I began to question whether I could carry on in the relationship despite 2 amazingly clever and handsome sons having been born - your song (let her go) came on the radio and the floodgates opened - they literally did not want to stop, I repeated the song at least 5 times, knowing very well the first time it came on, that your lyrics had spoken to me - my marriage was over because this man would never EVER  appreciate me until I left him. And so your song became poignant in that moment for that reason. A year later, free and happy I met the most wonderful man - we clicked instantly and I fell in love, we were inseperable and I finally was loved how I wanted to be. He died sadly in his sleep after we were together 6 months. He suffered with sleep apnea and stopped breathing. I moved my children and myself back to the UK heartbroken, to be near to my family and I started my life again alone. 6 months After Ian died, I happened to put this song onto YOU TUBE via my computer and my jaw dropped open...... The video for this song was you, yet my brain went into complete shock - it was literally like watching Ian through the TV! - your face looked exactly like Ian's, your clothes, your stature, your stance, you both played guitar - I never even knew that 'Passenger' was just a solo artist, yourself.... I sat on the kitchen floor watching the video for this song and I cried buckets and buckets and buckets - watching you in this video was like Ian coming back to life, and at the same time, your song was the anthem to the end of my 17 year relationship. Headfuck! Hahahaha.

All I can say is THANK YOU SO MUCH for writing this song - in 2 very different but both poignant ways - this 1 song and it's video have given me pleasure and pain - but such is the power of brilliant music that can do both those things to another human being, despite it being very rare I'm sure, that ONE song can be so poignant to one person for TWO very different reasons. Michael, please keep doing what you do. This song was clearly meant to reach me for two very meaningful, milestone reasons in my life and I am so very grateful to you that you wrote this song so that it could touch me in the way it has. You are a genius and I am so very grateful. Your lyrics have reached out to me during some truly tough moments in my life and I thank you so very much. x

Comment:
Dear person whoever reads this, 
Hey, you, yes, I am talking right to you. I hope you will see yourself with the eyes I see you one day, because I can tell you have some awesome music taste :) You‚Äôre such a beautiful human being and worth and enough. I hope you know that you do only need yourself to be happy, I know society build up the standard that whenever you‚Äôre alone you‚Äôre not living a happy live. But in fact that is not true, if you start to realize that you actually deserve all the good things happening to you, you will treat yourself a lot¬† nicer. I hope you let yourself rest, don‚Äôt beat yourself up over past mistakes, over regret, and over everything your mind wants to destroy you. I wish I could remove all those demons inside of your head because you deserve to feel happy. If you ever feel lonely then watch the sky, because you know, someone, at the same time is watching the sky too, maybe feeling the same way.I am glad you exist and I hope you won‚Äôt ever remove your own spot in this world, maybe you don‚Äôt feel like you belong here but, Angel, then build your home here. I don‚Äôt want you to leave this world unhappy. I want you to live every little second, I want you to feel alive, I don‚Äôt want you to see yourself just existing. You deserve it. Whatever happened, it‚Äôs not your fault, the demons in your head recognize that you have a beautiful heart, they want to take it because they have never seen such beautiful heart as yours, so why let them win over you? . You‚Äôre not selfish for isolating yourself, but you deserve to talk to someone. If you‚Äôre reading this than please never forget to breath and smile. 

Don‚Äôt live up to other standards! It‚Äôs your story and not theirs. 


Life for those who couldn‚Äôt, smile for those who forgot what a genuine smile is, love like there‚Äôs no other, hug like its your last one. 

I love you and send you hugs.
You‚Äôre so strong, you‚Äôre still here, and I am proud of you. 

AND REMEMBER:
YOU ARE NOT USELESS. READ THAT AGAIN. 
YOU ARE WORTH IT. READ THAT AGAIN.
YOU ARE LOVED. READ THAT AGAIN.
I AM GLAD YOU EXIST. READ THAT AGAIN.
YOU ARE NOT A PROBLEM. YOU ARE HUMAN AND YOUR FEELINGS ARE VALID. READ THAT AGAIN.

You‚Äôre not a burden to anyone, don‚Äôt be afraid to talk, to use your voice. 

You‚Äôre beautiful inside out. 

I LOVE YOU SO MUCH. READ THAT AGAIN.

I WISH I COULD HUGH YOU RIGHT NOW, SO A VIRTUAL HUG WILL DO. 


It hurts me to see you‚Äôre in pain :( you deserve so much better love, don‚Äôt let your emotions control you. Don‚Äôt let them get the best of you. 

I love you, I love you I love you I love you I love you please don‚Äôt go.

I am sorry that no one is hearing you, I am sorry no one is noticing that you have lost yourself. I wish I could take your pain away, it hurts me to see the pain in your eyes.¬† I love you trough my words and I mean it. I just want you to stay, hold on a little longer okay? Please? For me.??

I hope you have an awesome day/ morning/ evening/ night. 

If it‚Äôs night for you, go to sleep, I know it‚Äôs hard to fall asleep right now but you deserve a good sleep. If you have nightmares, please, don‚Äôt let them fight you. 

If it‚Äôs day for you, don‚Äôt start it by such sad music, I know it‚Äôs impossible to have a good day with such mindset but take baby steps, start by drinking two cups of water in the morning and so on.. You will start building little healthy habits. 

If it‚Äôs evening for you, you‚Äôre probably overwhelmed and stressed, I want you to know it‚Äôs okay to feel the way you feel. You don‚Äôt need to be scared, of course you‚Äôre overwhelmed or stressed, I mean who wouldn‚Äôt? But it‚Äôs important to know that when you feel that way you should do a little self care, such as taking a bath for example? You deserve to feel at ease and relaxed.


And if you are somewhere in between I hope you know that you‚Äôre stronger than you think, I know you will make it :) 

All I want for you is to stay and feel alive. 

Now wipe those tears away and smile for me, you really don‚Äôt know much a smile can brighten someone‚Äôs day, do you? I hope one day yours will become a genuine one where you don‚Äôt need to fake it anymore, because I can‚Äôt say this enough, you deserve a good smile and to feel alive. You‚Äôre worth more than every fucking cent in this world.

I need you here with me :). 

Remember crying is not weakness, let it out as much as you can but don‚Äôt let the emotion control you by giving up. It‚Äôs okay, you‚Äôre here, you‚Äôre safe, you can let it out.

Did anyone asked you, how you are feeling today? If not, how are you really? I don‚Äôt think you‚Äôre doing good, but you will feel good at one point. Don‚Äôt give yourself up. 

And anyone who gets to be with you, doesn‚Äôt know how fucking lucky he/ she/ they is :).

Enough with beating up yourself for today, okay?!

- The stranger that cares about you more than anything.

I hope this is enough for you to stay today, tomorrow will be a new day, a new start, let go now. I hope you can stay.

I hope you will remember my words :)

P.S: if you ever feel like you need to talk to someone here's my insta @anjara_ramia
